Checking the help when there are no arguments.

  $ ./main_base.exe return --help
  An empty command
  
    main_base.exe return 
  
  === flags ===
  
    [-help], -?                . print this help text and exit
  

  $ ./main_climate.exe return --help
  Usage: ./main_climate.exe return [OPTIONS]
  
  An empty command
  
  Options:
   --help, -h   Print help

